            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> Aha, maybe multiple events are registered for close flaoting. But we schedule the closing logic in the next time loop in the callback, and the delete of augroup is wrapped by pcall. So it continues to run. Could you try it to see if it works?\r\n\r\nYes, it eliminates the `Invalid window id` error, but `b:lsp_floating_preview` is still present in some cases.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nI edited `runtime/lua/vim/lsp/utils.lua` and tested various ways to close the floating window opened by pressing `K` or running `:lua vim.lsp.buf.hover()`.\r\n\r\nThe purpose is to understand which methods of closing the preview will make `winnr` invalid.\r\n\r\nI reused `minimal_init.lua` used in the original issue (#31289).\r\n\r\nIn short, when I close the preview using the following method, `winnr` is invalid in `close_preview_window()` and `b:lsp_floating_preview` is not deleted.\r\n\r\n- Run `:only` in the main window\r\n- Run `:close` in the preview\r\n- Run `:bdelete` in the preview\r\n- Press `q` in the preview\r\n\r\nMy impression is that it would be simpler and better to create an autocmd for `WinClosed` instead of defining `vim.w[winnr].buf_hold_win`.  `WinClosed` is triggered before the window is removed, so the window ID should be valid in its callback function.\r\n\r\nThis PR serves as a quick fix for a typo and the `Invalid window id` error, so even if we end up using `WinClosed`, I think that would be a separate issue and PR. (Excuse me, but I have other tasks I'd like to work from now on.)\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n<summary>diff: runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua</summary>\r\n\r\nThe purpose of this edit is to log what is happening.\r\n\r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git a/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua b/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua\r\nindex ae0f9c43e..349ecbe3f 100644\r\n--- a/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua\r\n+++ b/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua\r\n@@ -1336,7 +1336,19 @@ end\r\n ---@param winnr integer window id of preview window\r\n ---@param bufnrs table? optional list of ignored buffers\r\n local function close_preview_window(winnr, bufnrs)\r\n+  print(\r\n+    string.format(\r\n+      'close_preview_window: entered. winnr = %s, bufnrs = %s',\r\n+      winnr,\r\n+      vim.inspect(bufnrs)\r\n+    )\r\n+  )\r\n+  print('close_preview_window: nvim_list_wins() =', vim.inspect(api.nvim_list_wins()))\r\n+\r\n   vim.schedule(function()\r\n+    print('close_preview_window: schedule: entered')\r\n+    print('close_preview_window: schedule: nvim_list_wins() =', vim.inspect(api.nvim_list_wins()))\r\n+\r\n     -- exit if we are in one of ignored buffers\r\n     if bufnrs and vim.list_contains(bufnrs, api.nvim_get_current_buf()) then\r\n       return\r\n@@ -1344,11 +1356,24 @@ local function close_preview_window(winnr, bufnrs)\r\n\r\n     local augroup = 'preview_window_' .. winnr\r\n     pcall(api.nvim_del_augroup_by_name, augroup)\r\n+\r\n+    print('close_preview_window: schedule: winnr =', winnr)\r\n+    print('close_preview_window: schedule: windows =', vim.inspect(api.nvim_list_wins()))\r\n+\r\n     if api.nvim_win_is_valid(winnr) then\r\n+      print('close_preview_window: schedule: winnr is valid')\r\n+\r\n       local buf = vim.w[winnr].buf_hold_win\r\n+      print('close_preview_window: schedule: buf_hold_win =', buf)\r\n+\r\n       if buf and api.nvim_buf_is_valid(buf) then\r\n+        print('close_preview_window: schedule: buf_hold_win is valid')\r\n         vim.b[buf].lsp_floating_preview = nil\r\n+      else\r\n+        print('close_preview_window: schedule: buf_hold_win is NOT valid')\r\n       end\r\n+    else\r\n+      print('close_preview_window: schedule: winnr is NOT valid')\r\n     end\r\n     pcall(api.nvim_win_close, winnr, true)\r\n   end)\r\n@@ -1370,6 +1395,7 @@ local function close_preview_autocmd(events, winnr, bufnrs)\r\n   api.nvim_create_autocmd('BufEnter', {\r\n     group = augroup,\r\n     callback = function()\r\n+      print('event = BufEnter')\r\n       close_preview_window(winnr, bufnrs)\r\n     end,\r\n   })\r\n@@ -1378,7 +1404,8 @@ local function close_preview_autocmd(events, winnr, bufnrs)\r\n     api.nvim_create_autocmd(events, {\r\n       group = augroup,\r\n       buffer = bufnrs[2],\r\n-      callback = function()\r\n+      callback = function(ev)\r\n+        print('event =', ev.event)\r\n         close_preview_window(winnr)\r\n       end,\r\n     })\r\n```\r\n\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n<summary>Tests and results</summary>\r\n\r\n## Test 1. Move the cursor in the main window\r\n\r\n1. Press `K` to open the preview.\r\n2. Move the cursor in the main window by pressing j, k, etc.\r\n\r\n    This operation prints the following, and closes the preview.\r\n\r\n    ```text\r\n    event = CursorMoved\r\n    close_preview_window: entered. winnr = 1002, bufnrs = nil\r\n    close_preview_window: nvim_list_wins() = { 1000, 1002 }\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: entered\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: nvim_list_wins() = { 1000, 1002 }\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: winnr = 1002\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: windows = { 1000, 1002 }\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: winnr is valid\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: buf_hold_win = 1\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: buf_hold_win is valid\r\n    ```\r\n\r\n3. Run `:echo b:lsp_floating_preview`\r\n\r\n    This results in `E121: Undefined variable: b:lsp_floating_preview`.\r\n    `b:lsp_floating_preview` has been deleted.\r\n\r\n## Test 2. Move the cursor to the preview, then run `:close`\r\n\r\n1. Press `K` to open the preview.\r\n2. Press `K` again to move the cursor to the preview.\r\n\r\n    This operation prints the following:\r\n\r\n    ```text\r\n    event = BufEnter\r\n    close_preview_window: entered. winnr = 1002, bufnrs = { 2, 1 }\r\n    close_preview_window: nvim_list_wins() = { 1000, 1002 }\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: entered\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: nvim_list_wins() = { 1000, 1002 }\r\n    ```\r\n\r\n3. Run `:close` in the preview.\r\n\r\n    This operation prints the following, and closes the preview.\r\n\r\n    ```text\r\n    event = BufEnter\r\n    close_preview_window: entered. winnr = 1002, bufnrs = { 2, 1 }\r\n    close_preview_window: nvim_list_wins() = { 1000 }\r\n    event = CursorMoved\r\n    close_preview_window: entered. winnr = 1002, bufnrs = nil\r\n    close_preview_window: nvim_list_wins() = { 1000 }\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: entered\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: nvim_list_wins() = { 1000 }\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: entered\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: nvim_list_wins() = { 1000 }\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: winnr = 1002\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: windows = { 1000 }\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: winnr is NOT valid\r\n    ```\r\n\r\n4. Run `:echo b:lsp_floating_preview`\r\n\r\n    This results in `1002`.\r\n    `b:lsp_floating_preview` is present.\r\n\r\n## Test 3. Move the cursor to the preview, then run `:bdelete`\r\n\r\nThe same as Test 2.\r\n\r\n## Test 4. Move the cursor to the preview, then press `q`\r\n\r\nThe same as Test 2.\r\n\r\n## Test 5. Move the cursor to another window\r\n\r\n1. Create a new window with `:new`.\r\n2. Move back the cursor to the main window.\r\n3. Press `K` to open the preview.\r\n4. Press `CTRL-W_w` to move the cursor to another window.\r\n\r\n    This operation prints the following, and closes the preview.\r\n\r\n    ```text\r\n    event = BufEnter\r\n    close_preview_window: entered. winnr = 1003, bufnrs = { 3, 1 }\r\n    close_preview_window: nvim_list_wins() = { 1001, 1000, 1003 }\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: entered\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: nvim_list_wins() = { 1001, 1000, 1003 }\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: winnr = 1003\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: windows = { 1001, 1000, 1003 }\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: winnr is valid\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: buf_hold_win = 1\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: buf_hold_win is valid\r\n    ```\r\n\r\n5. Run `:echo b:lsp_floating_preview`\r\n\r\n    This results in `E121: Undefined variable: b:lsp_floating_preview`.\r\n    `b:lsp_floating_preview` has been deleted.\r\n\r\n## Test 6. Close the preview by running `:only` in the main window\r\n\r\n1. Press `K` to open the preview.\r\n2. Run `:only` in the main window.\r\n\r\n    This operation prints nothing, and closes the preview.\r\n\r\n3. Run `:echo b:lsp_floating_preview`\r\n\r\n    This results in `1002`.\r\n    `b:lsp_floating_preview` is present.\r\n\r\n4. If I move the cursor after `:only`, the following is printed:\r\n\r\n    ```text\r\n    event = CursorMoved\r\n    close_preview_window: entered. winnr = 1002, bufnrs = nil\r\n    close_preview_window: nvim_list_wins() = { 1000 }\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: entered\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: nvim_list_wins() = { 1000 }\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: winnr = 1002\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: windows = { 1000 }\r\n    close_preview_window: schedule: winnr is NOT valid\r\n    ```\r\n\r\n5. Run `:echo b:lsp_floating_preview`\r\n\r\n    This results in `1002`.\r\n    `b:lsp_floating_preview` is still present after `CursorMoved`.\r\n\r\n</details>",
